 <body>
  <p>The locations host the configuration of the displays according to where the various screens are.</p> 
  <p>This page shows creating and managing locations for Screens.</p> 
  <p><strong>Pre-requisites</strong>:</p> 
  <ul> 
   <li><a href="../../sites/deploying/using/configuring-screens-introduction.md">Configuring and Deploying Screens</a></li> 
   <li><a href="../../screens/using/creating-a-screens-project.md">Creating and Managing Screens Project</a></li> 
   <li><a href="../../screens/using/managing-channels.md">Creating and Managing Channels</a></li> 
  </ul> 
  <h2>Creating a New Location</h2>
  <p>Once you create your project for Screens, follow the steps below to create a new Location for a Screens project:</p> 
  <ol> 
   <li>Select the Adobe Experience Manager link (top left) and then Screens. Alternatively, you can ï»¿go directly to: <a href="http://localhost:4502/screens.html/content/screens">http://localhost:4502/screens.html/content/screens</a>.</li> 
   <li>Navigate to Screens project and click <strong>Locations</strong>. </li> 
   <li>Click <strong>Create</strong> next to the plus icon in the action bar. A wizard will open.</li> 
   <li>Select the template <strong>Location</strong> from the wizard and click <strong>Next</strong>.</li> 
   <li>Enter the properties for <strong>Title and Tags</strong>, <strong>More Titles and Description</strong>, <strong>On/Off Time</strong>, and <strong>Vanity URL</strong>.</li> 
   <li>Click <strong>Create</strong> and the location is created and added to your locations folder.</li> 
  </ol> 
  <p>See the steps below to understand creating a new location for an AEM Screens project. For demonstration purposes, the new location (SanJose) is created under <em>DemoProject</em>.</p> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/player2.gif" />
  <p>Once you create a location, you have to create a new display for your location.</p> 
  <h3>Editing Properties for a Location</h3>
  <p>To edit/access the properties of a location:</p> 
  <ol> 
   <li>Select the location.</li> 
   <li>Click <strong>Properties</strong> from the action bar.</li> 
  </ol> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/player3.gif" />
  <h4>The Next Steps</h4>
  <p>Once you create a location, you have to create a new display for your location. </p> 
  <p>See <a href="../../screens/using/managing-displays.md">Creating and Managing Displays</a> for more details.</p> 
